{"TopicId":82186,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"How fast do Kerbals run/walk?","CreatedByName":"Strainborm","CreatedById":116277,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-08-20T08:21:45Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Strainborm","CreatedById":116277,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-08-20T08:21:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EThe title says it \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E (in meters per second)\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222014-08-21T19:36:54Z\u0022 title=\u002208/21/2014 07:36  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00229 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 21, 2014\u003C/time\u003E by Strainborm\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Reactordrone","CreatedById":110060,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-08-20T08:38:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EA little bit over 1m/s. On long walks I\u0027ve found that they can go about 350m in 5 minutes which works out to roughly 1.16m/s\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"mhoram","CreatedById":78756,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-08-20T16:28:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EYou can make Kerbals considerably faster by using the Shift-key to make them sprint. 100 m in 45 sec on Kerbin.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AlexanderB","CreatedById":17544,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-08-20T17:33:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EMuch less so on low gravity bodies though, but in those places, you can speed up a bunch with jetpack. \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jett_Quasar","CreatedById":117851,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-08-21T05:20:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EDoing a physics warp (Alt \u002B \u0026gt;) will speed up the game and allow your Kerbal to appear to walk faster - less boring on long jaunts.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EJR\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Pecan","CreatedById":96332,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-08-21T10:30:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EYes, physics warp works too.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Geschosskopf","CreatedById":69507,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-08-21T12:16:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Jolly_Roger\u0022 data-cite=\u0022Jolly_Roger\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003EDoing a physics warp (Alt \u002B \u0026gt;) will speed up the game and allow your Kerbal to appear to walk faster - less boring on long jaunts.\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EBut they can\u0027t run fast enough to escape the Kraken! \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"peadar1987","CreatedById":81207,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-08-21T13:29:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Jolly_Roger\u0022 data-cite=\u0022Jolly_Roger\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003EDoing a physics warp (Alt \u002B \u0026gt;) will speed up the game and allow your Kerbal to appear to walk faster - less boring on long jaunts.\u003Cp\u003EJR\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAlthough sometimes this causes the Kerbals to spontaneously explode. You have been warned!\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}